<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">well first off any site that would give diablo 1 a 5/5 score and this game a 3.5/5 is deffinetly out of whack with reality anyways.So i take there review with a grain of salt.Another thing that really frustrates me is when people compare this to diablo 2,yes the interface looks somehwhat like Diablo 2 but this game is on a totally grander scale.Diablo 2 is so dang linear its not even funny.Divine divinity you can do what u want when u want,can u say that about diablo 2??? nope. divine divinity you have so many sidequests it will make ur head spin can you say that about diablo 2??? nope.In Divine divinity when you pick a class can you cross over and specialize in another class skill?? yes   can you do that in Diablo 2?? nope.Its to bad that people want to pass this off as a diablo clone because its not at all.This game has so much replay value its scary and i think reviewers forget to mention that.
I also have seen reviews where people take points off for a lack of a multiplayer when it never claimed to have one in the first place.thats just like a reviewer taking points off for a game like Ever quest because it doesnt have a single player,how can they do that??? My advice to you people is if you want to see the most honest scoring for games go to pc game review.com.Hundreds of players like you and i rate games and whatever it averages out to is usually a good indication of how good a game is.i tend to not listen to the so called proffesional reviewers because all to often there wrong.i would rather take the opinion of 100 people then 1.
Prime example most pro reviwers were saying diablo was a game of the likes never seen before and everyone should get it,heck i was seeing people giving it a 100/100.so then i bought it and omg what a pile of junk.At pc game website where us normal players review games its about 92/100 and it deserves to be that high/</TEXTAREA>
